1. Enter the command “git init” to initialize an empty Git repository.
2. Enter command “git add .” to add all local files to the local Git repository
3. Enter the following command to commit your local files to the local Git repository. 
At this point however, the files are not added to your Git repository on the internet because these files are locally committed.
git commit -m "first commit"

4. Now to create a remote setup, copy the below URL from GitHub:
“git remote add origin https://github.com/……../mybasproject.git”
5. Enter the “git push” command to move all the locally committed files to the GitHub repository.
git push --set-upstream origin main
6. You can clone an existing repository using the following command:
“git clone https://github.com/………../mybasproject.git“

